# Search for 'loss', 'focal', or 'adaptive' in the text and print a larger window around them

matches = list(re.finditer(r'(adaptive focal loss|focal loss|loss function|loss)', text, re.IGNORECASE))

for i, match in enumerate(matches[:3]):
    start = max(0, match.start() - 500)
    end = min(len(text), match.end() + 1500)
    print(f'--- Match {i+1} ---')
    print(text[start:end])
    print('\n---\n')
